<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-18T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-18T02:00:00-05:00" n="281" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d281">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/17886:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-18T10:00:00+03:00">December 18, 1941—10
                                    a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 19—6:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2077. The Counselor of the British Embassy<note n="34" xml:id="d281fn34">Herbert Lacy Baggallay, Acting Counselor of the British
                                Embassy.</note> informed me last night that Sikorski, acting on
                            reports of impending American, British and Soviet discussions, has
                            addressed a message to Stalin asserting the claim of Poland to
                            participate. His claim apparently was based upon, among other
                            considerations, the fact that Poland was among the first victims of
                            Hitler’s war of aggression and the opinion “that Poland is the
                            touchstone of the probity of the ideology of the Allies[”].</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>